R410 *BUMPERS must be supported. BUMPERS must be supported by the structure/frame of the ROBOT

Most of our bumper mounting points will be directly on the frame. We have two points where there are two steel rods bolted to the frame, which supports a steel top plate, across those two short rods. Can we bolt bumpers to this steel plate? Does this count as ‚Äústructure‚Äù since it‚Äôs not the frame? It‚Äôs plenty solid, just making sure inspectors aren‚Äôt going to flag that.

These are exactly where we need a mount point for the bumpers.
